{Even if White can take over the complete control of the position by blocking
on e4 and so on, Black has a chance of building up a passive but hard to break
fortress. Here is such a typical case when White failed to find the right
method at the critical moment.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 d6 4. Nc3 g6 5. e4 Bg7
6. Bd3 O-O 7. Nge2 e6 8. O-O exd5 9. cxd5 Ne8 10. Be3 Nd7 11. f4 a6 12. a4 b6
13. Rb1 Bb7 {[#]Black has taken some measures against the main plan, but with
the pawn on e4 still the bishop is passive on b7. This allows White widening
the theater of operations:} 14. Qd2 Rc8 15. b4 Nef6 16. h3 Re8 17. Bf2 Qc7 18.
b5 a5 {Since ...c5-c4 would just allow Nd4-c6, Black is doomed to passivity.}
19. Bc2 h6 20. Rbe1 Qb8 21. g4 Nh7 22. Bg3 Re7 23. e5 {Finally the thematic
break.} dxe5 24. f5 g5 {The same policy as on the queenside: Black tries
keeping the position blocked on both wings.} 25. d6 Ree8 26. Ne4 Nhf6 27. N2c3
Rcd8 28. Rd1 Nxe4 29. Bxe4 Bxe4 30. Nxe4 Qb7 31. Qg2 Qa8 32. f6 Bh8 33. Rf5 Re6
{[#]Everything has goe White's way but now he stumbles on the way to
converting his advantage.} 34. Rdf1 $6 ({There was no need for defending f6
and White should have opened the kingside at once:} 34. h4 $1 Nxf6 (34... Bxf6
35. Rdf1 $16 {is no better.}) (34... gxh4 35. Bxh4 $18 {defends the pawn and
prepares a slow but decisive attack:} Nf8 36. Rh5 Ng6 37. Rxh6 Nf4 38. Qc2 $18)
35. Nxf6+ Bxf6 36. Qxa8 Rxa8 37. Rxf6 $1 Rxf6 38. d7 Rd8 39. Bxe5 $16 {
threatening Bc7. Black needs finding a way to play with a bishop down but
White has every chance to win.}) 34... Nf8 $1 {After this well-timed
regrouping Black is in time to stop the enemy initiative.} 35. h4 gxh4 36. Bxh4
Ng6 37. Bg3 ({The familiar} 37. Rh5 {runs into} Nf4) 37... Rdxd6 $1 {The the
simplest way of neutralizing White's threats.} (37... Qd5 38. Rh5 Qd4+ 39. Kh2
{maintains White's pressure.}) 38. Nxd6 Qxg2+ 39. Kxg2 Rxd6 {Due to his
stability on dark squares Black has enough compensation for the exchange.} 40.
Kh3 Re6 41. g5 hxg5 42. Kg4 e4 43. Kxg5 Nf8 44. Be5 e3 1/2-1/2

