{[#]White continued his attack with} 25. Bxb6 Nxb6 26. Qh6 {leaving Black
little choice:} Nxd5 {How would you answer the pawn grabbing?} 27. Nxd5 $2 ({
This allows Black escape dry out of deep trouble. Correct was} 27. Be6 $1 {
Reminiscent of Rogozenco's Be6.} Nxf6 (27... Nxc3 28. Bxf7+ Kxf7 29. Qxh7+ Ke6
30. Nc5+ Kd5 31. Nxb7 {also offers White a decisive attack while}) (27... fxe6
28. f7# {mates.}) 28. Bxf7+ $1 Kxf7 29. Qxh7+ Ke6 30. Nc5+ Kd6 31. Nxb7+ Kc6
32. Nxd8+ $18 {with an extra exchange and a continuing attack.}) 27... Bxd5 28.
Ng5 Bxf6 29. Qxh7+ Kf8 30. Be6 Bxg2+ $1 ({The saving move. If} 30... Bxe6 31.
Nxe6+ Ke7 32. Nxd8 $16) 31. Kg1 Qa7+ 32. Kxg2 Rd2+ 33. Kh3 Rd3+ 34. Kg2 Rd2+
35. Kh3 Rd3+ 1/2-1/2

