{[#]Black was caught on the wrong foot, but reacted with the thematic} 22... e4
{Your move.} 23. Nfxe4 $6 ({White should have kept his light-squared bishop at
any cost, as this piece is very important for the attack:} 23. Qh3 $1 Ne5 24.
Bb3 (24. Ba2 $5) 24... Qd8 ({Or if} 24... c4 25. Bc2 Bxd5 26. Nfxe4 {/\f6, Ng5}
Nd3 27. f6 Bxe4 28. fxg7 Kxg7 29. Nxe4 Rxe4 30. Bxd3 cxd3 31. Qd7 $40 {with a
continuing attack.}) 25. Nfxe4 Bc8 26. Bc2 Bxf5 (26... Nc4 27. Bg5 {is also
promising for hite.}) 27. Rxf5 $1 {Finally putting the bishop to work.} gxf5
28. Ng5+ Kh8 29. Qxf5 Nf6 30. Nh7 Neg4 31. Nxf8 $14 {hite retrieved the
exchange with obvious advantage.}) 23... Ne5 24. Qe2 Nxc4 25. Qxc4 Bd4+ 26. Kh1
({Or if} 26. Be3 Bxd5 27. Qxd5 Qxd5 28. Nxd5 Rxe4 29. fxg6+ Kxg6 30. Bxd4 Rxe1
31. Rxe1 cxd4 32. Rd1 $11 {with a probable draw. ***Ater the last move the
simplest way to equality was 26...Re5.}) 0-1

