{[#]Apart from the familiar plan of blocking on e4, White has the permanent
threat d5-d6. Your move.} 18... bxa4 $1 {Indeed, this is the best. Black
clears the path for the knight to d4, turning d5 into a weakness.} 19. Nxa4 (
19. Bxa4 Rxb2 20. Qc1 {allows} Rxf2 $5 21. Rxf2 e4 22. fxg6 hxg6 23. Ngxe4 Nb6
$15 {with excellent compensation for the exchange.}) 19... Nb5 20. Nxc5 Nd4 21.
Nxd7 ({It may have been better fighting against the central knight with} 21.
Nb3 $5 {even though after} Nxc2 22. Qxc2 Bb7 {Black's play remains more
pleasant.}) 21... Bxd7 $17 {White's attack has come to an end and Black
retains very active play.} 0-1

