{[#]Black has played the opening highly originally and now hoped to win
material with} 12... Nb6 {Your move.} 13. e5 $3 {Of course! Queen retreats
would allow ...axb5 with unclear play. The central break immediately takes
advantage of the exposed king's position, even though it implies sacrificing
the queen.} dxe5 ({The point is that after} 13... Nxa4 14. exf6+ {the king is
in lethal danger.} Kf8 ({Or if} 14... Kxf6 15. Rxe8 Qc7 16. Bg5+ Kf5 17. Bd3+
Kg4 18. Re4+ Kh5 19. Rh4#) 15. Rxe8+ Qxe8 16. fxg7+ Kxg7 17. Bxe8 $18) 14. Qa3
$1 {Another important move.} Kf8 ({There is no time for} 14... axb5 $2 {due to}
15. Qxc5+ Qd6 16. Rxe5+ Kd7 17. Re7+ Qxe7 18. Qc7#) 15. Bxe8 exf4 16. Qxc5+ Kg8
17. Ba4 (17. Bxf7+ Kxf7 18. d6 {followed by Re7 would have yielded a decisive
attack with approximately equal material.}) 17... Nxa4 18. Nxa4 Nxd5 19. Rad1 {
Black does not have compensation for the lost exchange and could not save the
game despite stubborn defense.} 1-0

