{[#]Black has played according to the familiar plan but White's queenside
activity should not be neglected. How would you continue?} 18... Nxh2 $1 {
The only way of keeping the initiative going.} ({If} 18... Ne5 19. Be2 $14 {
White not only threatens Bxa6 but also plans to consolidate with Ne3, b3 and
so on.}) 19. Kxh2 g4 $1 $15 {This pawn is very helpful for creating the threat
of a strong attack along the h-file.} 20. Bxg4 ({Relatively best.} 20. Be2 {
offers Black free hands:} Qh4+ 21. Kg1 Re5 $1 22. Rb3 Rh5 23. Rh3 gxh3 24. g3
h2+ 25. Kh1 Qh3 26. Ne3 (26. Bxh5 Qxf1+ 27. Kxh2 Qh3+ 28. Kg1 Qxh5 $19) 26...
Rh6 27. Ng2 b5 $17) 20... Bxg4 21. Ne3 (21. f3 {weakens the dark squares too
uch:} Qh4+ 22. Kg1 Be5 23. g3 Qxg3+ 24. Qg2 Bh3 25. Qxg3+ Bxg3 26. Rf2 f5 $17)
(21. Kg1 Bf3 $1 $17 {dooms the e4 pawn since the bishop is taboo:} 22. gxf3
Qg6+ 23. Kh1 Re5 $19) {And now Black should have continued with:} 21... Qf4+
22. Kg1 (22. g3 Qh6+ 23. Kg1 Bf3 24. Ng2 Qh3 $19) 22... Rxe4 23. f3 (23. Nxg4
Qxg4 24. Rxd6 Re2 $17) 23... Rxe3 24. fxg4 Qe4 25. Qf2 Re2 26. Qxf7+ Kh8 $17
1/2-1/2

