{[#]The resolute advance of the kingside pawns has cleared space for Black's
pieces. And yet, White thought his coordination is enough for keeping things
under control when playing} 32. Be1 $2 {For reasons you will discover yourself
it was essential neutralizing the g7-bishop with 32.Bc3. Do you see a way of
punishing the game move?} Nxf3 $1 33. gxf3 Qh5+ {It appears that White's
pieces are too far for providing the king with the needed protection.} 34. Kg1
(34. Kg2 Qh3+ 35. Kf2 Qh2+ 36. Ke3 Bd4# {Now and in other lines we understand
why 32.Bc3 was better.}) (34. Qh2 Qxf3+ 35. Qg2 Bxe4 $19) 34... Qxf3 35. Ra4
Bd4+ (35... Kh8 $1 $19 {[%cal Ge8g8]}) 36. Rxd4 cxd4 37. Nf6+ Kf8 38. Nxe8 Bxd3
39. Qf2 Qxf2+ 40. Bxf2 Kxe8 41. Bxd4 Be4 $19 {[%csl Gd6,Gh6]} 42. Kf2 Bxd5 43.
Ke3 Ke7 44. Bc3 Bb3 45. Kf4 Ke6 46. Bg7 h5 47. Bf8 Bd1 48. Bg7 h4 49. Bd4 h3
50. Bg1 Be2 0-1

