{3[#]The bishop's ueenside influence is obvious, but is there a way to
increase its pressure on the other wing, too?} 31... g4 $1 {Indeed, this
clears the attacking h4-d8 diagonal for the queen, threatening to weaken the
kingside structure with ...gxf3 at the same time.} 32. Bd4 $2 {In vain hoping
to exchange the bishop.} (32. fxg4 $2 {allows} Qh4 33. g3 Rxg3+ 34. hxg3 Qxg3+
35. Bg2 Nh4 36. Rb2 (36. Qd2 Nf3+) 36... Bxb2 37. Qxb2 Nf3+ 38. Kf1 Qe1#) ({
White should have accepted a clearly worse position after, say,} 32. Bf2 gxf3
33. g3 $17) 32... Bxh2+ $1 33. Kxh2 Qh4+ 34. Kg1 g3 35. Bxa6 Rxf3 $2 ({A
unnecessary sacrifice. Black had several wins, the most clear-cut being} 35...
Rc2 $1 36. Bd3 Qh2+ 37. Kf1 Qh1+ 38. Bg1 Rf2+) 36. gxf3 Qh2+ 37. Kf1 $18
1/2-1/2

