(12. Kh1 {is usually played with the following idea:} a6 13. Bxd7 Bxd7 14. f5 {
After exchanging the knight, White has o problems weakening the e5-square.} Qe7
$5 $146 {I find this move to be the most solid. The queenside counterplay will
follow naturally but for the time being it is essential to secure the kingside.
} 15. Bg5 f6 16. Bf4 Rfe8 17. Bg3 ({Preparing Nh4. If} 17. Qd2 b5 18. fxg6 hxg6
19. Nh4 g5 20. Ng6 Qf7 21. Bxd6 Qxg6 22. Bxc5 a5 23. axb5 f5 {White does not
seem to have entirely adequate compensation for the piece.}) 17... Bf8 18. Bh4
{Allowing ...g7 if needed to defend g6.} g5 ({If Black does not have anything
against a draw he can also play} 18... Bg7) 19. Bg3 b5 {The f8-bishop fulfills
