1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 e6 4. Nc3 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. f3 Bg7 8. Nge2
O-O 9. Ng3 {Developing the knight with the bishop on c1 aims at achieving the
regrouping based on Nh1-f2 in time.} h5 {Immediately starting the fight
against the knight.} ({For reasons which will be revealed later, it is better
to delay} 9... a6 10. a4) 10. Bg5 {The critical answer, aiming to more or less
gain a tempo over the normal Bg5 lines.} (10. Be2 {is less challenging.} Nh7 ({
It is better not to drive the knight to e3 yet. The threat sometimes is
stronger than its execution.} 10... h4 11. Nf1 Nh7 12. Ne3 $5 $146) 11. Be3 ({
The point behind the previous move is that} 11. O-O Bd4+ {forces} 12. Rf2 $17 {
in order to leave h1 free for the knight.}) 11... h4 ({Once again inserting} 
11... a6 12. a4 {offers White additional ideas:} h4 13. Nf1 Qe7 14. Nd2 f5 15.
Nc4 $1 f4 {Yevseev,D (2455)-Gladyszev,O (2390) Tula 1998 (½-½, 22)} 16. Bxf4
$1 Rxf4 17. Nb6 Nd7 18. Nxa8 Bd4 {In the absence of the f-pawn Black's
compensation may not be sufficient.}) 12. Nf1 Qe7 13. Nd2 (13. Bf2 a6 14. a4 f5
15. exf5 h3 16. g3 Ng5 17. Ne3 Bd4 18. Qd2 Nd7 $132) 13... f5 {and White
cannot prevent the blockade with ...f5-f4 as his bishop is hanging and the
aforementioned tactical resource is not available.}) 10... Qb6 {Unpinning the
knight with gain of time. With ...a6 and a4 on board, the queen could
experience some temporary problems. For instance 12.Qd2 Nh7 13.a5! forcing her
releasing the pressure on b2.} 11. Qd2 ({After} 11. Qb3 {White's queen will
need more time to get back on the normal track than Black's.} Qc7 $1 12. Be2 a6
13. O-O (13. a4 Nh7 14. Be3 Qe7 15. O-O Nd7 16. f4 Bd4 17. Bf2 h4 18. Nh1 g5
19. Qd1 Qf6 $13 20. fxg5 $6 {½-½ Dreev,A (2645)-Topalov,V (2700) Elista 1998}
Qg7 21. Bxd4 cxd4 22. Nb1 Nxg5 $15) 13... Nh7 14. Be3 h4 $5 15. Nh1 f5 16. exf5
Bxf5 17. Nf2 (17. Bf2 g5 18. f4 gxf4 19. Bxh4 Bd4+ 20. Nf2 Nd7 21. Kh1 Ne5 $17
{Dreev,A (2690)-Bologan,V (2655) Shanghai 2001 (0-1, 41)}) 17... Nd7 18. Nce4
Rae8 19. Rfe1 Ndf6 20. Bd3 b5 21. Nxf6+ Nxf6 22. Bxf5 gxf5 $132 {Vasilevich,T 
(2395)-Arakhamia Grant,K (2452) Kishinev 2005 (0-1, 48)}) 11... Nh7 12. Bh4 {
The most ambitious move.} (12. Be3 {leads to normal play.} Nd7 13. Rb1 (13. Be2
h4 14. Nf1 Ne5 $15 {Thaler,T (2154)-Pavlovic,M (2461) Biel 2000 (0-1, 31)})
13... Ne5 14. Be2 h4 15. Nf1 Qd8 16. Bh6 f5 17. Bxg7 Kxg7 18. f4 Nf7 19. Ne3
fxe4 20. g4 hxg3 21. hxg3 Qe7 22. b4 b6 23. Qb2 Kg8 $11 {Glotov,M (2345)
-Gladyszev,O (2434) Dagomys 2009 (0-1, 47)}) 12... Nd7 13. Be2 (13. f4 {
exposes the centre allowing} c4 $5 $146 14. Bxc4 Nc5 $36 {with obious
counterplay as the king cannot get castlet short.}) 13... a6 {A refined
half-waiting move in a moment when ...b7-b5 is not a threat.} (13... g5 $6 {
is premature:} 14. Bxg5 Nxg5 15. Nxh5 Nh7 16. Nxg7 Kxg7 17. g4 {The difference
with respect to the main line is that after} Qb4 {White has} 18. Nb5 $16 {
winning the third important pawn for the piece, or the simpler 18.0-0-0 over
defending d4.}) 14. a4 ({If} 14. O-O c4+ 15. Kh1 {Svetushkin,D (2552)-Denny,K 
(2365) Turin 2006 (1-0, 39)} Qd4 16. Qf4 {White needs keeping the queen in
order to save the bishop.} Qc5 17. Be7 ({If} 17. a4 {Black has several good
neutral moves but he can also win the bishop with} f6 $5 {with just reasonable
compensation for White.}) 17... Re8 18. Bxd6 g5 19. Bxc5 gxf4 20. Nxh5 Nxc5 21.
Nxg7 Kxg7 22. Bxc4 Bd7 $13) 14... g5 $1 {With the new queenside configuration
this is good now.} 15. Bxg5 Nxg5 16. Nxh5 Nh7 17. Nxg7 Kxg7 18. g4 Qb4 {
The main idea is to reduce the attacking potential with a well-timed ...Qd4.}
19. a5 ({One important point is that now} 19. O-O-O $2 b5 $1 {offers Black a
strong attack. And of course 19.Nb5 is not available any more.}) 19... b5 (
19... Qd4 $15 {is also good, leaving Wite with just some compensation (two
pawns) for the piece.} 20. Qxd4+ $6 cxd4 21. Na4 Ne5 22. Nb6 Rb8 23. f4 Ng6 24.
f5 Ne5 $17 {hite is not in time to defend his pawn mass properly, facing
threats as ...Nf6 and ...d4-d3.}) 20. axb6 Nxb6 21. h4 Bd7 22. h5 f6 23. Rc1
Ng5 $17 {Vidit,S (2648)-Darini,P (2496) Dubai 2016 (0-1, 38)} *

