{[#] Coordinating the minor pieces is the biggest challenge for the Benoni
player. How will achieve it in this position?} 1... Nf6 {Preparing ...Bg4 or
even ...Bf5.} 2. h3 Na6 {The threat ...Nb4 is very unpleasant as the bishop
has almost no mobility and is tied up to the defence of the e4-pawn.} 3. a3 Bf5
4. Ng5 h6 5. g4 {White is trying to protect the e4-pawn in a tactical way.
Black's position is fine but energetical play is required.} c4 $1 {This is a
step in the right direction. The advance c5-c4 opens the important a7-g1
diagonal and frees the c5-square for the knight.} 6. Bc2 hxg5 7. gxf5 Nc5 {
Black managed to put a tremendous pressure the e4-pawn. White's position is
about to collapse.} *

