{[#] In this structure, White's dark-squared bishop is not optimally placed on
f4. How Black can seize the initiative in this position?} 1... Nh5 $1 {Of
course, now White must waste one more tempo to move his bishop.} 2. Be3 f5 {
Black makes use of his lead in the development and starts a direct kingside
play.} 3. Nge2 Qh4+ 4. g3 {This position was reached in the game Drozdovskij,Y
(2462)-Kislinsky,A (2412) Evpatoria 2001. How could have Black obtained a
significant edge in this position?} Nxg3 $1 5. Nxg3 f4 {Black manages to
regain the sacrificed piece and spoil the pawn structure of his opponent.} *

