{[#] This is a very important theoretical position. What is Black's best way
to handle it?} 1... h5 $1 {Immediately starting to chase the enemy knight,
before the h1-square becomes available for regrouping with Nh1-f2.} 2. Be2 h4
3. Nf1 Rb8 $1 {This flexible, and in my opinion, best move has been played
only once. Black makes a generally useful move (in the long run ...b7-b5 will
be possible) waiting for Nd2 to play the most active knight move ...Nh5.} *

