{[#] It seems that White has a solid positional edge due to the weakness of
a5-pawn and the restricted mobility of the e5-knight. How can Black create
counterplay here?} 1... Bxe2 $1 {Every true Benoni expert would love to get
rid of his light-squared bishop.} 2. Nxe2 Nb6 $1 {Another precise move. Black
is heading for the important c4-square.} 3. R4a2 a4 {This move is the last
element of Black's queenside counterplay. Now, one of Black's knight will
inevitably land on the c4-square.} *

