{[#] White's last move 14.Bg5 is designed to prevent the advance h5-h4. Does
Black run out of counterplay?} 1... h4 $1 {Nevertheless! It turns out that the
move Bg5 doesn't stop this advance.} 2. Nge2 ({The move} 2. Bxh4 $2 {is well
met by} Nxe4 $1) 2... h3 $1 {This is a thematic way to spoil White's kingside
structure.} 3. g4 Ne5 {It turns out that White has nothing better than playing
Ng1. Black's initiative is overwhelming.} *

