{[#] By means of the advance b2-b4 White intends to open up the position on
the queenside. At the same time, by deflecting the c5-pawn, he can occupy the
important d4-square. Try to create dynamic counterplay.} 1... cxb4 2. Nxb4 f4
$1 {Making use of the exposed knight on b4.} 3. Bf2 ({Of course, the move} 3.
Bxf4 $4 {is impossible due to} Qb6+ {winning the knight.}) 3... g5 {Black
managed to fortify his knight on the central e5-square and start active
actions on the kingside. Later on, he can follow with Qf6 and g5-g4.} *

