{[#] White has just played 9.Ng3. Developing the knight with the bishop on c1
aims at achieving the regrouping based on Nh1-f2 in time. How should Black
react in this case?} 1... h5 $1 2. Bg5 {The critical answer, aiming to more or
less gain a tempo over the normal Bg5 lines.} Qb6 $1 {Unpinning the knight
with gain of time. With ...a6 and a4 on board, the queen could experience some
temporary problems. For instance 12.Qd2 Nh7 13.a5! forcing her releasing the
pressure on b2.} *

