{[#] White decided to attack by means of the thematic f4-f5 advance. In this
position, however, this idea is not very sound since white knights are far
away from the e5-square. How should Black reorganize his forces?} 1... Qe7 $1 {
Very strong novelty. With his last move Black prepares the maneuver Nc5-d7-e5.}
2. Qf3 Ncd7 3. Qf2 Ne5 {After establishing a powerful knight on e5, Black has
nothing to complain about. Later on, he will connect his rooks by means of ...
Bd7 and will start playing on the queenside.} *

